Privacy Policy for Jot

Effective date: [Insert date]

Jot is a food diary app designed to help users log meals, ingredients, portions, notes, and related nutrition information.

This Privacy Policy explains what information Jot handles, how it is used, and what choices users have.

1. Information stored in the app

Jot may store the following information on your device:

* Meals and food diary entries
* Ingredients, quantities, calories, and nutrition information
* Favourite, recent, or repeated foods/meals
* Profile or preference information used to make food logging easier
* Notes you choose to add
* App settings and local app data

This information is used to provide the core food logging features of the app.

2. Local storage

Jot is designed to work locally on your device. Food logs and app data are stored on your device unless a feature clearly requires information to be sent elsewhere.

Deleting the app may delete locally stored app data from your device.

3. Information sent outside your device

Jot does not sell your personal data.

Depending on the features you use, Jot may send limited information outside your device to provide app functionality. This may include:

* Search terms, barcode numbers, food names, meal descriptions, or ingredient information used to look up or interpret food entries
* Images or text you choose to submit for menu, label, or food interpretation features
* Bug reports or diagnostic information if you choose to send feedback

Information sent for these purposes is used to provide the requested feature, improve reliability, investigate bugs, and support the app.

4. Third-party services

Jot may use third-party services to support features such as food lookup, barcode lookup, image/text interpretation, diagnostics, hosting, or app distribution.

These services may process limited information needed to provide those features. Jot does not use this information for advertising or sell it to data brokers.

5. Health and nutrition information

Food diary and nutrition data can be personal. Jot uses this information only to provide food logging and related app functionality.

Jot is not a medical device and does not provide medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment.

6. Analytics and advertising

Jot does not use third-party advertising.

